==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reveille
<hw>Re*veil"le</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧veil</ets>, fr. <ets>r⟦eacute⟧veiller</ets> to awake;
pref. <ets>re-</ets> re- + pref. <ets>es-</ets> (L. <ets>ex</ets>) +
<ets>veiller</ets> to awake, watch, L. <ets>vigilare</ets> to watch. The
English form was prob. taken by mistake from the French imper.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧veillez</ets>,<ets>2d</ets> pers. pl. See
<er>Vigil</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>The beat of drum, or bugle
blast, about break of day, to give notice that it is time for the
soldiers to rise, and for the sentinels to forbear challenging.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Sound a <xex>reveille</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For at dawning to assail ye⟦br⟧
Here no bugles sound <qex>reveille</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

